# Conventional Commits

All commit messages **must** follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format.

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **Type** (required): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `build`, `ci`, or similar.
- **Scope** (optional): area of the codebase, e.g. `midi`, `ui`, `docs`.
- **Description** (required): short imperative summary, lowercase after the colon, no period at the end.
- **Body** (optional): longer explanation; wrap at 72 characters.
- **Footer** (optional): e.g. `BREAKING CHANGE:`, `Refs #123`.

## Examples

```text
feat(docs): auto-connect to Icarus MIDI and show connection status
fix(midi): handle disconnected device in state change
docs: add conventional commit rule
chore(deps): bump eslint to 8.x
```

## Rules

- Use **imperative mood** in the subject: "add" not "added", "fix" not "fixed".
- Keep the subject line under **~50 characters** when practical.
- Do **not** end the subject with a period.
- When committing on behalf of the user, always use this format.
